result.name: CROWD RESTAURANT

reviews.text: For lunch (&dinner). Great stir fried dishes! Plenty of choices if you want something else. Free soup fcfs. Half a hundred can get you out of here.
Good food, reasonable price. Tight space between tables.
Taste good n reasonable price.

food: surprised to find the stewed pomelo skin! the ginger & scallion fish head in clay pot, and century eggs soup veggie are great too. slightly on the salty side (i guess the chefs are older chefs)
service: attentive, friendly!!
enviro: clean cantonese resto with 2-3 outdoor tables. they provide a table cloth!!! so so rarely seen in hk.
price: $100 average each dish + “tea charge”. it’s $370 for me eating alone, but the food i ordered was enough for 3 people.
verdict: a great place to enjoy classic cantonese stir-fry and clay pot dishes with friends and family!
tasty local food

result.name: 群眾小廚

reviews.text: 炒野夠 鑊氣，蒸餸就比較普通

點了干燒伊麵和凍奶茶，味道俱不佳，而且收費有點含糊，也較附近餐廳為貴。
I order fried noodle and iced milk tea, taste is not good. Pricing is not clear enough and quite high.
好味道,多人一齊黎食更佳
我的午餐飯堂，生炒骨，咖哩牛腩必食👍🏻
不錯，有幾個餸的確可以再叫！
